Sorting:

Arrays.sort(arr): Sorts an array in ascending order.
Arrays.sort(arr, Comparator): Sorts an array using a custom comparator.
Collections.sort(list): Sorts a list in ascending order.
Searching:

Arrays.binarySearch(arr, key): Searches for a key in a sorted array using binary search.
String Manipulation:

str.charAt(index): Returns the character at the specified index in a string.
str.substring(start, end): Extracts a substring from a string.
str.split(regex): Splits a string into an array of substrings based on a regular expression.
str.trim(): Removes leading and trailing whitespace from a string.
str.indexOf(substring): Returns the index of the first occurrence of a substring.
List Manipulation:

list.add(element): Adds an element to the end of a list.
list.remove(index): Removes the element at the specified index from a list.
list.get(index): Retrieves the element at the specified index from a list.
list.size(): Returns the number of elements in a list.
Map Manipulation:

map.put(key, value): Adds a key-value pair to a map.
map.get(key): Retrieves the value associated with a key from a map.
map.containsKey(key): Checks if a map contains a specific key.
map.keySet(): Returns a set of all keys in a map.
Math Operations:

Math.max(a, b): Returns the maximum of two values.
Math.min(a, b): Returns the minimum of two values.
Math.abs(num): Returns the absolute value of a number.
Math.pow(base, exponent): Returns the result of raising a base to an exponent.
Input/Output:

Scanner: Read input from the console or other sources.
BufferedReader: Read input using buffered input streams.
System.out.println(str): Print a string to the console.
Data Structures:

ArrayList: Dynamic array implementation.
LinkedList: Doubly linked list implementation.
HashMap: Hash table implementation for key-value pairs.
HashSet: Implementation of a set using a hash table.
Conversion:

Integer.parseInt(str): Converts a string to an integer.
String.valueOf(obj): Converts an object to a string.
Character.isDigit(char): Checks if a character is a digit.
Error Handling:

try-catch blocks: Handle exceptions gracefully.